[3] Chile (Osorno, Puerto Montt)
Date: Wed 4 Apr 2012
Source: EMOL [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.emol.com/noticias/nacional/2012/04/04/534253/isp-confirma-nuevos-casos-de-hantavirus-37-personas-contagiadas-en-el-pais.html


A 19-year-old man who is in the Linares Hospital has been added to the list of individuals confirmed infected by [a] hantavirus. This information was provided by the Institute of Public Health (ISP) and brings to 37 the number of people who have acquired the virus [infection] so far in 2012. [Note: this individual unfortunately died the following day, see the report above].

There are 2 more confirmed cases that include a 45-year-old man who is in the Hospital Base of Osorno and a 29-year-old man who is being attended to in the Hospital Base of Puerto Montt. These 2 cases were reported by the Universidad Austral de Valdivia Reference Laboratory, which is part of a network of clinical laboratories for hantavirus confirmation.

