[4] Chile (Puerto Montt, Los Lagos region)
Date: Wed 4 Apr 2012
Source: EMOL [in Spanish, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.emol.com/noticias/nacional/2012/04/04/534279/fallece-en-puerto-montt-trabajador-de-29-anos-contagiado-con-virus-hanta.html


A 29-year-old worker from Puerto Montt has become the 6th person to die due to [a] hantavirus [infection]. The young man had been in the Hospital Base of the city since Sun 1 Apr 2012 at noon, according to reports from Radio BioBio.

The family of the worker indicated that the man began to feel ill last Tuesday [27 Mar 2012] and decided to go to the hospital on Sat 30 Mar 2012.

The hospital carried out the rapid test that confirmed the detection of the virus.

